cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about instance-level human analysis, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques to analyze human instances in images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes an end-to-end pipeline that involves deep learning models, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also presents state-of-the-art results on several datasets, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves analyzing human instances, which could raise privacy concerns, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category as well.
